sql:
SELECT AVG(decision_count) AS average_decisions_per_case
FROM (
    SELECT case_id, COUNT(decision_id) AS decision_count
    FROM decisions
    GROUP BY case_id
);

external_knowledge:
- 'Closed' status refers to cases that are no longer active or open;
- 'Primary user' refers to the main user assigned to a case;
- 'Tagged with decision' means the case has a specific tag indicating a decision has been made.

- "phoenix rising from the ashes" refers to active cases that have been revived or are ongoing;
- "gathered a quiver of evidence" refers to cases with the topic category and tag name 'evidence';
- "more than five updates" means the case has been updated more than five times;
- "recent decision after the dawn of the new decade" means the most recent decision date is after January 1, 2020.

- "Legal garden" refers to the legal system or legal cases in a metaphorical sense;
- "Dawn of the new decade" refers to January 1, 2010;
- "End of the 2010s" refers to December 31, 2020.

- 'Recent updates' refers to updates made within the last 30 days;
- 'Linked to an appeal' means the case has a related case with a link type of 'appeal';
- 'Most recent update' is the latest update text and date for each case.
